CAPE TOWN The Hawks have confirmed that they are investigating certain aspects of the Gupta emails. Hawks confirms to Parly Committees they are investigating certain aspects of Gupta emails. "We can't arrest before we investigate."In June, media began reporting on more than 100,000 documents and emails leaked from inside the business empire of the Gupta family, which is close to President Jacob Zuma.The Guptas have said the leaks are fake and have denied wrong-doing.However, the Hawks on Wednesday told parliament that they are investigating certain aspects of those emails.The Hawks also confirmed to DA MP David Maynier that the case he opened against Gupta's, for the lavish wedding at the Sun City resort and allegations of money laundering is being investigated. The Hawks confirm they are now investigating the charges laid by myself against the Guptas relating to the family wedding in Sun City!READ: Meanwhile, On Tuesday the Hawks informed that they did not clear the president s son, Duduzane Zuma and the Guptas of state capture allegations.The elite crime fighting unit said the president s son must provide proof of his claims after he said the Hawks found no evidence of wrongdoing against him or the Guptas.He made the claims in an open letter to former Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan.Zuma accuses Gordhan of unfairly targeting him and his business partners. eNCA